  "texts": [
    "Since h is harmonic, the bundle E admits a holomorphic structure such that Φ is a holomoprhic section of K Σ ⊗ End(E) (cf.",
    "[AABC + 19, Appendix A]).",
    "From this, we obtain the following lemma which is well-known to experts.",
    "Let ρ ∈ Hom red (π 1 (B), G) be a reductive representation, h: Σ → (G/K, g sym) a ρ-equivariant harmonic map.",
    "If (P, Φ) is a G-Higgs bundle representing the gauge equivalence class corresponding to ρ under the non-abelian Hodge correspondence, then tr Φ 2 = 0 ∈ H 0 (Σ, K 2 Σ) if and only if h is weakly conformal.Proof."
